(secondQuint)Simvastatin in Patients With Isolated Arterial Hypertension.

 Hypertension is one of the most important predictors of cardiovascular diseases (CVD).

 Due to the fact that hypertension frequently coexists with hypercholesterolemia and diabetes which increase the risk of CVDs development, it is advisable to use the optimal combined therapy (hypotensive + hypolipidemic + hypoglycemic)in this group of patients.

 Statins are the most effective and widely used drugs for the treatment of hypercholesterolemia.

 According to the available experimental and clinical data they may decrease the blood pressure (BP) in normotensive and hypertensive patients.

 However, it is still difficult to determine to what degree the reduction of both blood pressure and cardiovascular risk is due to hypotensive or hypolipidemic/pleiotropic effects of statins.

